<TITLE> Halt to bail for sugar traders stays </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Oct 27 (bdnews24.com)The Supreme Court has upheld an order halting bail to 14 sugar traders of Jessore in two cases on charges of illegally hoarding huge stocks of sugar. The five-member Appellate Division bench headed by chief justice M M Ruhul Amin on Tuesday ordered the government and the traders to make arrangements for hearing of the bail petition in the High Court. The High Court granted the 14 traders bail on Oct 6 but the Appellate Division chamber judge halted the order the next day following a government petition. Additional attorney general M K Rahman represented the state while TH Khan and M A Zahir argued for the traders. The traders are Hafizur Rahman, Safiar Rahman, Rafiqul Islam, Modhusudan Saha, Alok Kumar Kundu, Sirajul Islam, Sarwar Hossain, Abdul Wahab, Anisur Rahman aka Boro Anis, Anisur Rahman aka Chhoto Anis, Abdul Odud, Raju Ahmed, Mohammed Momin and Chittaranjan Kundu. Agriculture marketing officer in Jessore Sujaet Hossain Khan filed the cases on Oct 1 under the Special Powers Act for hoarding sugar worth Tk 16 crore. One case was filed for hoarding 3,910 sacks of sugar and another for 67,100 sacks of sugar illegally. On Sept 26, RAB, police and National Security Intelligence officials in a raid on four stock houses of Joint Trading Corporation and Sheikh Brothers seized sugar worth Tk 16 crore. bdne
